139→### Orb Count Clamping
140→
141→Uniform arrays are fixed at 8 elements. The host code **must** clamp `u_orbCount` to a maximum of 8 before uploading uniforms. If the consumer provides more than 8 orbs, only the first 8 are rendered and a console warning is emitted:
142→
143→```typescript
144→const MAX_ORBS = 8;
145→
146→function setOrbs(orbs: OrbRenderConfig[]) {
147→  if (orbs.length > MAX_ORBS) {
148→    console.warn(`OrbKit: WebGL renderer supports a maximum of ${MAX_ORBS} orbs. Only the first ${MAX_ORBS} will be rendered.`);
149→  }
150→  const clamped = orbs.slice(0, MAX_ORBS);
151→  gl.uniform1i(orbCountLocation, clamped.length);
152→  // ... upload clamped orb uniforms
153→}
154→```
